page 22 (
    name: Edit
    alias: EDIT7
    title: Edit
    appearance {
        pageTemplate: @/standard
        templateOptions: #DEFAULT#
    }
    navigation {
        warnOnUnsavedChanges: false
    }
    javaScript {
        functionAndGlobalVariableDeclaration: var htmldb_delete_message='"DELETE_CONFIRM_MSG"';
    }
    css {
        inline:
            ```css
            .ui-slider {
                width: 180px;
                margin: 8px;
            }
            ```
    }
    security {
        authorizationScheme: mustNotBePublicUser
        pageAccessProtection: argumentsMustHaveChecksum
        formAutoComplete: false
    }
    advanced {
        reloadOnSubmit: always
    }
    help {
        helpText: No help is available for this page.
    }

    region about-this-page (
        name: About this page
        type: staticContent
        source {
            htmlCode:
                ```html
                <p>This page contains two dynamic actions called 'SALARY HIGH' and 'CALC COMMISSION'.</p><p>'SALARY HIGH' fires whenever the value of the 'Salary' slider has changed and checks if the salary is greater than 5000. If the salary is greater than 5000 the salary display field is set to red. If the salary is less than or equal to 5000 the salary display field is set to green.</p><p>'CALC COMMISSION' does a similar job as in the 'Set Value (PL/SQL)' example (firing an AJAX call to retrieve the commission and highlighting the 'Commission' page item), only this time, it is being fired when the value of the 'Salary' slider changes.</p>
                <p>'SALARY HIGH' uses one native action ('Add Class') in combination with an event raised by one plug-in item type ('Slider').</p>
                <p>'CALC COMMISSION' uses one native action ('Set Value' with a 'Set Type' of 'PL/SQL Function Body') and one plug-in action ('Highlight').</p>
                
                ```
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 10
            slot: body
        }
        appearance {
            template: @/blank-with-attributes
            templateOptions: #DEFAULT#
        }
    )

